          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Santa Cruz’s legacy is fundamental for thinking about Afro-Peruvian women’s narratives. Her work demonstrates that identity is not only spoken but also performed, felt, and remembered through the body. By reclaiming rhythm, movement, and voice, she created a space where Afro-Peruvian women could articulate their presence beyond stereotypes and exclusion. In this sense, her practice is not only artistic—it is deeply political, offering a way to resist erasure and to imagine new forms of being and belonging."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
